  "body": "From: https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/issues/806#issuecomment-417987842\r\n\r\n### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nWe have some defaults that are used to quiet down some noisy loggers:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/v0.2.0-alpha.31/trinity/utils/logging.py#L111-L114\r\n\r\nWere the use to supply overrides to these via the command line they would not be respected\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nThis lines should be relocated such that they are merged with the user supplied logging levels before being passed into `setup_log_levels`.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/blob/v0.2.0-alpha.31/trinity/main.py#L111-L112\r\n",
