    "body": "@glaksmono \r\n\r\n> Do we want [1] to keep those noisy logs at INFO level (i.e as current, less noisy) then overrides it when log level is defined from the command line?\r\n\r\nYes, this.  If no cli flag is provided, then `p2p.kademlia` and `p2p.discovery` should still be set to `INFO`.   But, if `--log-level p2p.kademlia:DEBUG` were specified via CLI then the `p2p.kademlia` level should be set to `DEBUG`.",
